SAA workers and union members sing and dance during a picket protest outside the OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways (SAA) staff will finally get the outstanding balance of their November salaries. Employees only got 50 percent of their wages at the beginning of the month. READ: Flight Centre clips SAA's wings The cash-strapped airline said released the payment of the other 50 percent on Friday. SAA says it regrets the inconvenience caused by the delay.